create(address,uint256,uint256,uint256,u.details: Uses CREATE2 for deterministic addresses and requires the caller to have yield management permissions on the token. params.endTime: The timestamp when yield distribution should end (must be after startTime)
params.interval: The interval between yield distributions in seconds (must be > 0)
params.rate: The yield rate in basis points (1 basis point = 0.01%, e.g., 500 = 5%)
params.startTime: The timestamp when yield distribution should start (must be in the future)
params.token: The ERC20Yield-compatible token to create the yield schedule for

returns._0: The address of the newly created yield schedule
